Biography

2023: Did not see game action

2022: Did not see game action

2021: Saw action in two games ... Made his Duke debut in a win over Merrimack, registering one shot (8/29).

Prior to Duke: Played his youth career at Nevada United and the Reno 1868 USL Academy team (2020-21) ... Helped Nevada United win two US Club Soccer West Regional Cups (2018 & 2019) ... Won two NorCal NPL 2 Fall League Championships and one NorCal NPL 2 Spring League Championship ... Davis Legacy Showcase finalist ... Named Best XI at the Davis Legacy Showcase ... 2018 US Club Soccer National Cup champion ... Competed in several other sports in high school ... Four-year letterwinner in basketball ... Two-time rebound leader ... 2019 & 2018 Second Team All-League honoree ... 2019 Mammoth Tournament MVP ... Two-year letterwinner in swimming ... Qualified for regionals in the 50 Free (2018 & 2019) ... Qualified for the 4x50Free relay at state ... One year letterwinner in track & field ... 2021 Regional Champion in the 100m, 400m, Long Jump and 4x400m ... One year letterwinner in golf ... Qualified for the 2018 regionals ... Class Valedictorian ... Golden Scorpion Winner for a high honors diploma + 12 seasons of varsity sports.

Personal: Son of Ted and Erin Mulvaney ... Has two younger siblings; sister, Libby and brother, Caleb ... Father, Ted, is a Duke class of 1991 alumni ... Cousin, Mary Jane Erving, played soccer at Oregon ... Cousin, James, plays baseball at McGill University ... Born on July 24, 2003.
